# Cookie Care – Phase A Core Endpoint Smoke Tests
# Usage: open in VS Code REST Client, IntelliJ HTTP Client, or run with httpYac.
# Set @baseUrl and @token before running.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3001
@token = <YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN>

###
# ── 1. Upload a contract document ──────────────────────────────────────────
# POST /api/contracts/upload
# Returns { data: ContractDocument } with status=UPLOADED
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/contracts/upload
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "filename": "sample-nda.txt",
  "mimeType": "text/plain",
  "content": "NON-DISCLOSURE AGREEMENT\n\nThis Agreement is entered into as of 1 Jan 2026 between Party A and Party B.\n\n1. CONFIDENTIALITY\n   Each party agrees to keep the other party's confidential information secret.\n\n2. TERM\n   This Agreement shall remain in force for a period of two (2) years.\n\n3. GOVERNING LAW\n   This Agreement shall be governed by the laws of India."
}

# Expected: HTTP 201 – { "data": { "id": "...", "status": "UPLOADED", ... } }
# Copy the returned `id` into @contractId below before running the next requests.

###
# ── 2. Ingest the uploaded contract ────────────────────────────────────────
# POST /api/contracts/:id/ingest
# Transitions status UPLOADED → INGESTING → READY (Phase A stub)
# Replace <CONTRACT_ID> with the id from step 1.
@contractId = <CONTRACT_ID>

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/contracts/{{contractId}}/ingest
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

# Expected: HTTP 200 – { "data": { "id": "...", "status": "READY", ... } }

###
# ── 3. Check contract status ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# GET /api/contracts/:id/status
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/contracts/{{contractId}}/status
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

# Expected: HTTP 200 – { "data": { "id": "...", "status": "READY", ... } }

###
# ── 4. Ask a question about the contract ───────────────────────────────────
# POST /api/ask
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/ask
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "contractId": "{{contractId}}",
  "question": "What is the term (duration) of this agreement?"
}

# Expected: HTTP 200 – { "data": { "answer": "..." } }

###
# ── Health: Auth login (obtain a token for use above) ──────────────────────
# POST /api/auth/login
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "your@email.com",
  "password": "YourPassword123!"
}

# Copy the returned accessToken into @token above.
